Author: Ben
Version: 7.0
Requires: Executor with Drawing API and HttpGet support

Overview

AimRare Hub v7.0 is a fully customizable client-side enhancement script for Roblox, featuring a configurable legit-style aimbot, advanced ESP visualization tools, and an expanded Fluent UI interface.
This version focuses on customization, improved prediction handling, and simplified input logic.

Key Features
Legit Aimbot

Configurable FOV-based targeting

Smooth camera interpolation

Optional hit chance simulation

Adjustable prediction speed for improved movement leading

Team check, alive check, and wall check options

Selectable aim parts (Head, UpperTorso, HumanoidRootPart)

Fluent-based keybind control for aiming

ESP System

Supports several on-screen overlays for player visualization:

Box ESP

Skeleton ESP (R6 and R15)

Name ESP

Health Bar ESP

Distance display

Customizable ESP color through Fluent's colorpicker

Automatic caching and cleanup per player

Fluent UI Integration

Version 7.0 replaces previous UI handling with full native Fluent controls:

Toggles, sliders, dropdowns

Keybind configuration

Colorpickers for FOV and ESP colors

Organized tab layout (Legit Aim, Visuals, Settings)

Optional watermark display

Built-in unload button for safe cleanup

Changelog (v7.0)

Integrated Fluent's native keybind and colorpicker systems

Added configurable prediction speed for dynamic target leading

Simplified input handling using Fluent's state-based keybind API

Updated visuals to support dynamic color updates from UI

General cleanup and internal restructuring for improved readability and performance

Requirements

To run this script successfully, the executor must support:

Drawing API (Drawing.new)

HttpGet for loading the Fluent UI library

Stable RenderStepped execution

Performance will depend on hardware and the number of active Drawing objects.

How the System Works
Aimbot Processing

Selects the closest viable target within the configured FOV radius.

Applies alive, team, and wall checks when enabled.

Calculates predicted aim position using distance-based time and user-defined prediction speed.

Interpolates the camera toward the predicted target location using a smoothing factor.

Applies configured hit chance before executing aim logic.

ESP Rendering

Maintains a cache of Drawing objects per player.

Projects character positions onto the screen each frame.

Draws ESP elements such as boxes, names, skeletons, health bars, and distances if enabled.

Handles per-player cleanup when characters or players are removed.

Configuration

All core adjustable values are stored in the Settings table, for example:

AimbotEnabled = false
AimbotFOV = 100
AimbotSmooth = 0.2
AimbotHitChance = 100
PredictionSpeed = 1000
AimPart = "Head"
BoxESP = false
SkeletonESP = false
NameESP = false
HealthESP = false
TeamCheck = false
WallCheck = false
ShowWatermark = true


Most settings can also be modified directly through the Fluent UI.

Script Unloading

The script includes an unload function accessible in the Settings tab.
Executing it will:

Disconnect the RenderStepped loop

Remove all Drawing objects

Clear ESP caches

Remove the FOV circle and watermark

Destroy the Fluent UI window

This ensures clean termination without requiring a client restart.
